    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer underflow in UE_thread timestamp calculations\n\n### Summary\nThere is an integer underflow producing an unexpectedly large unsigned value downstream of function UE_thread. The issue occurs when calculating writeTimestamp with mixed signed/unsigned arithmetic operations.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/nr-ue.c`: Added proper casting to (int64_t) for get_samples_slot_timestamp return values to prevent integer underflow in arithmetic operations\n- Fixed timestamp calculation in UE_thread function where uint32_t was being used in signed arithmetic\n- Applied similar fixes to related functions that use get_samples_slot_timestamp for consistency\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with specific timing advance values, the UE can experience unexpected behavior due to the large timestamp values generated by the integer underflow. This manifests as:\n- Incorrect TX timing \n- Potential buffer overflows in downstream processing\n- Unpredictable UE behavior during slot processing\n\nThe issue is most likely to occur when the timing advance values cause the timestamp calculation to underflow, resulting in extremely large positive values due to unsigned integer wraparound.\n"
}